82. Implement the setcookie( ) function with various arguments using the PHP program.
<?php
// Start output buffering to avoid header issues
ob_start();

// Set various cookies

// 1. Basic cookie (expires in 1 hour)
setcookie("basic_cookie", "BasicValue", time() + 3600);

// 2. Cookie with path restriction (only works in '/')
setcookie("path_cookie", "PathValue", time() + 3600, "/");

// 3. Secure cookie (only sent via HTTPS, may not show on localhost)
setcookie("secure_cookie", "SecureValue", time() + 3600, "/", "", true);

// 4. HttpOnly cookie (inaccessible via JavaScript)
setcookie("httponly_cookie", "HttpOnlyValue", time() + 3600, "/", "", false, true);

// 5. Secure + HttpOnly cookie
setcookie("full_cookie", "SecureHttpOnly", time() + 3600, "/", "", true, true);
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>PHP setcookie() Example</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>üç™ PHP setcookie() Example</h2>

<?php
if (!empty($_COOKIE)) {
    echo "<h3>Cookies available (after refresh):</h3>";
    echo "<ul>";
    foreach ($_COOKIE as $key => $value) {
        echo "<li><strong>$key</strong>: $value</li>";
    }
    echo "</ul>";
} else {
    echo "<p>Cookies have been set. Please <strong>refresh the page</strong> to see their values.</p>";
}
?>

</body>
</html>

OUTPUT 
PHP setcookie() Example
Cookies available (after refresh):
PHPSESSID: qr92k91mkeuv9rmjvd9mlpsnra
test_cookie: CookieValue123
basic_cookie: BasicValue
secure_cookie: SecureValue
httponly_cookie: HttpOnlyValue
full_cookie: SecureHttpOnly

